nodes.title: Loop Notes
widgets_values:
Looping works by loading the last video you generated, extracting it's last frame and continuing from there.
DO NOT run the workflow in loop mode until the previous video finishes or it'll pick the wrong video. Do not queue multiple batches, same issue.

The directory is set in the Select Latest node on the left. We also save to that directory by default, so it will pick up the next video automatically. If you modify the path do it in both the select latest node and the video combine node.


tl;dr:
1. With loop Disabled, generate your first video.

2. Enable Loop. You may disable the video processing and run the workflow to collect the last frame to preview & update the prompt as needed. 

3. Enable both loop and process video to generate the next video chunk.

Don't like a generation? Just delete it from your output folder and continue. Try again if it errors loading the file.




Join the video chunks together with ffmpg when you're done:


# Step 1: Define output list file
$listFile = "filelist.txt"

# Step 2: Clear or create the file
if (Test-Path $listFile) { Remove-Item $listFile }
New-Item -ItemType File -Path $listFile -Force | Out-Null

# Step 3: Write full paths in ffmpeg concat format
Get-ChildItem -Filter *.mp4 | ForEach-Object {
    $fullPath = $_.FullName.Replace("'", "''")  # Escape single quotes
    Add-Content -Path $listFile -Value "file '$fullPath'"
}

# Step 4: Run ffmpeg to concatenate
ffmpeg -f concat -safe 0 -i $listFile -c copy output.mp4
